# F-Droid / FOSS compliance

Full guide: [docs/development/fdroid-compliance.md](../../docs/development/fdroid-compliance.md)

## Never add without explicit approval

- Google Play Services, Firebase, GMS, Crashlytics, ads, analytics
- Proprietary USB/audio SDKs or binary blobs
- Dependencies with unknown, NC, or “free for development only” licenses
- Runtime-loaded assets from external CDNs

## Allowed licenses (typical)

Apache-2.0, MIT, BSD, ISC, GPL-compatible, LGPL (source vendored — e.g. libusb).

## Before merging a new dependency

```bash
./gradlew :app:dependencies --configuration debugRuntimeClasspath | tee /tmp/deps.txt
# CI fails if gms|firebase|play-services appear
```

Confirm license in upstream repo. Native code must build from source in this tree (submodule or vendored).

## App license

Contributions are **GPL-3.0-or-later** ([LICENSE](../../LICENSE)).
